<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddcff7a93-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s2086"><num value="2086">§ 2086.</num><heading> Definition</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this part, the term “Member of the House of Representatives” means a Representative in, or a Delegate or Resident Commissioner to, the Congress.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddcff7a94-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/696/tVIII/s806">Pub. L. 100–696, title VIII, § 806</ref>, <date date="1988-11-18">Nov. 18, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4610">102 Stat. 4610</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddcff7a95-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddcff7a96-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddcff7a97-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was classified to section 188a–5 of former Title 40, prior to the enactment of Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works, by <ref href="/us/pl/107/217/s1">Pub. L. 107–217, § 1</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1062">116 Stat. 1062</ref>.</p>
</note>
